Condition : 9 - Prior to commencement of the above groundworks, Landscape and Ecological Enhancement and Management Plan shall be submitted to the local planning authority and approved in writing, and shall include (but not limited to):
A. details of all biodiverse roofs (including the Biosolar roofs) including details of extensive substrate base, features to be included within the substrate e.g. rope coils, sand, gravel, etc., and details of any seeding/plug plant choice (in accordance with The Gro Green Roof Code 2021);
B. details of invertebrate habitat such as a stag beetle loggery and bee bricks; 
C. orientation, target species and location for all swift and bat boxes/ bricks to be integrated with the new buildings; 
E. a bat sensitive post-construction lighting plan, including lux spill diagrams, to ensure that any lighting will be of a specification that minimises its impacts on bats, onsite and adjoining habitats, in accordance with the BCT and ILP 2023 Guidance Note (including having a colour temperature of <2700k and no uplighters.
F. details on the landscape management to be implemented post-construction shall also be submitted, which shall include management responsibilities and maintenance schedules for all hard and soft landscaped areas as well as the above-mentioned measures to provide biodiversity gain. 
The approved details shall be installed prior to the occupation of the development, and retained and maintained as such unless otherwise agreed by the local planning authority.
Reason: To ensure a satisfactory appearance and biodiversity value in the development, in accordance with Council policies LP1, LP55 and LP56 of the Local Plan. The details are required prior to the commencement of works to ensure the landscaping measures are incorporated in the layout and construction of the development.
